 API functions can be edited (add, remove) and executed by address contained in {Register_Authorities} list (Defined in the "Register" inherited contract)

 @param agora Address of Agora contract

Add_Contract(address,bytes,bytes).details: Add a third party smart contract to the API (it's address is added to {Contract} mapping and {List_Contracts} list)

params.contract_address: Address of the third party smart contract to add to the API
params.description: Text describing the smart contract and justifying it's add to the API. Can be a hash
params.name: Name of the smart contract.

Add_Function(address,bytes4).details: Add a third party smart contract's function to the list of functions callable via the API.

params.contract_address: Address of the third party smart contract.

Execute_Function(address,bytes).details: Make a call to a function of a third party smart contract belonging to the API

params.contract_address: Address of the third party smart contract
params.data: Data corresponding to the function call. It's a bytes composed by the function selector + encoded parameters. It correspond to the field {data} of a transaction.

Get_Contract_List_Functions(address).details: Get the list of all function selector of a contract registered in the API.

Get_Functions_By_Selector(address,bytes4.details: Get the receipts of all call to a function of a contract registered in the API. It also returns the index of the function selector in the contract structure's {List_Functions} array.

Get_List_Contract().details: Get the list of all third party smart contract registered in the API.

Remove_Contract(address).details: Remove a third party smart contract from the API

params.contract_address: Address of the third party smart contract to remove from the API

Remove_Function(address,bytes4).details: Remove a function from the list of third party smart contract's functions callable via the API

params.contract_address: Address of the third party smart contract.
params.function_selector: Function selector of the function to remove.

Set_Constitution(address).details: The function Allows to change the Constitution contract the current Institution obey to. The function is only callable by the {Constitution_Address}

params.new_constitution: Address of the new Constitution contract.

Set_Param(address,bytes,bytes).details: Modify the name and description of third party contract registered in the API

params.contract_address: Address of the third party smart contract.
params.name: New name of the contract.

constructor.details: Add the address of Agora Contract to {Register_Authorities}.

Constitution_Address().notice: Address of the constitution of the DAO

Remove_Authority(address).notice: Removes an account address from the {Register_Authorities}
